The paper discusses deep reinforcement learning algorithms and their ability to transfer existing skills to novel tasks, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also focuses on continuous control problems, which are often studied in robotics (cs.RO). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel approach for policy composition, which could be relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and control systems (cs.SY).
